title: [IOTDB-805] Fix BufferUnderflowException when querying TsFile stored in HDFS
body:
As is described in issue #1503 , `BufferUnderflowException` when querying TsFile stored in HDFS is caused by the unflushed `outputstream` when calling `endChunkGroup()` method in `TsFileIOWriter`.

Besides, this PR also fixes some **POTENTIAL** bugs that **MAY** cause error when users config HDFS for TsFile storage.

title: [IOTDB-799]remove log visualizer code and doc
body:
I notice the logVisualizer tool lacks docs, and seems there is nobody using it.

Besides, there is no UT/IT for the tool.

Therefore, I'd like to remove the module from our repo to keep the source code safety and clear.

If someday we find it useful, we can get it back from the git history.

[IOTDB-766] fix release unclosed file reader bug
body:
The query reader reference is increased correctly in FileReaderManager.

However, as the QueryFileManager mix up the closed and unclosed file, the unclosed reader reference is not decreased correctly in FileReaderManager.

title: [Distrubuted] Fix startup checkstatus and optimize some related logic
[distributed]change gc pause time  and the core pool size
Support double quotation in Path and optimize the Path String usage
Remove backup and support auto registration in InsertTabletPlan
body:
This pull request removes the backup logics. Instead of replicating the full InsertPlan, some containers with prefix name "failed" in InsertPlan, as well as its subclasses, reserves the information of the failed timeseries, which comsumes less memory.

This pull request also implements auto registration if the InsertTabletPlan contains any non-existent timeseries.

title: delete timeseries when path is not found
body:
Problem >>> If the DeleteTimeseriesPlan is routed globally and the metadata is removed, and the other node needs to retrieve the full paths, then the metadata is nowhere to be found.

Solution >>> In this implementation, the full paths will be retrieved before plan routing.
